# Adding to the End

Sometimes you want to add content to the end of a file without deleting existing content. For `file_put_contents()`, use the `FILE_APPEND` flag.

```php
file_put_contents('log.txt', 'New entry', FILE_APPEND);
```

With `fopen()`, use mode `'a'` (append).

```php
$handle = fopen('log.txt', 'a');
fwrite($handle, 'New line\n');
fclose($handle);
```

```php
<?php
// Using file_put_contents
echo file_put_contents('log.txt', '[' . date('Y-m-d H:i:s') . '] User logged in\n', FILE_APPEND);

// Using fopen/fwrite
$handle = fopen('log.txt', 'a');
if ($handle) {
    fwrite($handle, 'Another log entry\n');
    fclose($handle);
}
?>
```
